    Test Procedure for a VisAD Release to the ftp Server

1. on local machine, in the visad-build directory:
  
  svn update
  ant clean
  ant build
  ant jar.examples

2. cd testing

3. runall.bat

4. if successful, close the RMI Registery window and then proceed:

   cd \visad-build
   ant dist
   ant jar.source

5. cd \visad-build
   type DATE  // note the last release date
   copy core\build\DATE .

6. svn log -v > log.txt
     and then edit to remove all lines since last release

7. ftp ftp.ssec.wisc.edu
   
   cd /pub/visad
   put DATE
   bin
   put visad_examples.jar
   put visad_doc.jar
   put visad_src.jar
   put visad.jar
   mkdir <svn version>
   cd <svn version>
   put DATE
   put visad_examples.jar
   put visad_doc.jar
   put visad_src.jar
   put visad.jar

8. check the sizes....

9. ssh 'www' & cd /var/apache/www/htdocs/visad-docs
   ftp ftp and bin, get "visad_doc.jar"
   cd javadoc
   unzip ../visad_doc.jar  -- replace All
   cd ..
   rm visad_doc.jar

9. clip < log.txt

10. send out an email to "visad-list@unidata.ucar.edu"

11. browser to https://mcidasv.ssec.wisc.edu and log in
11a. go to: https://mcidasv.ssec.wisc.edu/projects/visad/news and
click "Add news"
11b. put in title "VisAD library update <date>"
11c. past log.txt with a lead-in line ("changes since last update on
<date>)

11. you are done!!

